---
import ProviderLayout from "../layouts/ProviderLayout.astro";
---

<ProviderLayout title="About" provider="About" description="About ANDO, its philosophy, and design principles.">
  <section id="philosophy" class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-bold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Philosophy</h2>
    <blockquote
      class="mb-6 border-l-2 border-zinc-200 pl-4 text-lg text-zinc-500 italic dark:border-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-400"
    >
      From the Latin <span class="not-italic">"and≈ç"</span> - to set in motion.
    </blockquote>
    <p class="mb-4 text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">
      ANDO is a typed build and deployment system that uses plain C# instead of YAML or custom DSLs. Build scripts are
      real code with full IDE support, type checking, and refactoring capabilities.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-4 text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">
      Every build runs inside a Docker container, ensuring clean and reproducible results regardless of your local
      environment. The CLI manages container lifecycle automatically.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="principles" class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-bold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Design Principles</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-3 text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="font-bold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400">1.</span>
        <span
          ><strong class="text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">Plain C#</strong> - No custom syntax or DSLs. If you know C#,
          you know ANDO.</span
        >
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="font-bold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400">2.</span>
        <span
          ><strong class="text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">Typed operations</strong> - Compile-time errors catch mistakes
          before they run.</span
        >
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="font-bold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400">3.</span>
        <span
          ><strong class="text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">Containerized</strong> - Every build runs in Docker for isolation
          and reproducibility.</span
        >
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="font-bold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400">4.</span>
        <span
          ><strong class="text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">Single file</strong> - One <code
            class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 text-sm dark:bg-zinc-800">build.ando</code
          > file defines your entire workflow.</span
        >
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="font-bold text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400">5.</span>
        <span
          ><strong class="text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300">No ceremony</strong> - Just write code. No configuration files,
          no plugins to install.</span
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="how-it-works" class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-bold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">How It Works</h2>
    <p class="mb-4 text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">
      When you run <code
        class="rounded border border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-100 px-1.5 text-sm dark:border-zinc-700 dark:bg-zinc-800"
        >ando</code
      >, the CLI:
    </p>
    <ol class="mb-4 list-inside list-decimal space-y-2 text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">
      <li>
        Parses your <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 text-sm dark:bg-zinc-800">build.ando</code> file using Roslyn
      </li>
      <li>Registers all operations as steps in a workflow</li>
      <li>Starts (or reuses) a Docker container</li>
      <li>
        Mounts your repository to <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 text-sm dark:bg-zinc-800">/workspace</code>
      </li>
      <li>Executes each step in sequence</li>
      <li>Reports results and copies artifacts back to host</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">
      Warm containers are reused between runs for faster iteration. Use <code
        class="rounded border border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-100 px-1.5 text-sm dark:border-zinc-700 dark:bg-zinc-800"
        >ando run --cold</code
      > to force a fresh container.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="links" class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="mb-3 text-xl font-bold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Links</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">
      <li>
        <a href="https://github.com/andorei/ando" class="text-cyan-600 hover:underline dark:text-cyan-400"
          >GitHub Repository</a
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://www.nuget.org/packages/ando" class="text-cyan-600 hover:underline dark:text-cyan-400"
          >NuGet Package</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</ProviderLayout>
